msgstr ""

# 18cf4a716b7441c69519093926e2b1b2
#: ../../admin-guide/installation/index.en.rst:42
msgid ""
"A complete version number is made of a version-triplet: "
"``MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH``."
msgstr ""

# 885ce3a756224071aea28e2990be663a
#: ../../admin-guide/installation/index.en.rst:44
msgid ""
"As of v4.0.0, there are no longer any development (or unstable) releases."
" All releases are considered stable and ready for production use. "
"Releases within a major version are always upgrade compatible. More "
"details are available on the `New Release Processes "
"<https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/TS/Release+Process>`_ wiki "
"page."
msgstr ""

# 72eacccb85604023a8db891764e5e26f
#: ../../admin-guide/installation/index.en.rst:51
msgid ""
"Sometimes we speak of *trunk*, *master* or *HEAD*, all of which are used "
"interchangeably. Trunk and master, or sometimes TIP or HEAD, refer to the"
" latest code in a Git version control system (also referred to as a "
"*repository* or *Git repo*). Master is always kept releasable, and "
"compatible with the current major release version. Incompatible changes "
"are sometimes committed on a next-major release branch; for example, we "
"have the ``5.0.x`` branch where changes incompatible with 4.x are "
"managed."
msgstr ""

